Apple Mac, HP laptop and Playstation 4 among thieves' daylight haul from home
3:03pm Sunday 1st May 2016 in
Thieves have targeted a home on Helmsdale, making off with jewellery and electronic equipment.
The house was broken into between 2pm and 4.10pm on Wednesday, April 27. The thief, or thieves, made off with an Apple Mac, an HP laptop and a Playstation 4 as well as jewellery.
Wiltshire Police are now appealing for witnesses. A police spokesman said: "If you saw or heard anything suspicious in this area, at this time, please contact police on 101."
